cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with object recognition and localization in computer vision, which is a core topic in the field of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also incorporates textual co-occurrence statistics from web documents, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The optimization problem used in the paper can be considered as a machine learning algorithm, which is a common topic in both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.LG (machine learning) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with datasets such as ImageNet and Sun, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis (cs.MM).
